Requires extensions to implement org.apache.james.lifecycle.api.Startable or similar SPI interfaces.

Introducing Spring Boot would:

Add unnecessary complexity and bloat.

Conflict with Jamesâ€™s own classloader or lifecycle management.

Require custom wiring and bootstrapping which James doesn't expect.

âœ… Why a Plain Java Extension is Correct
âœ… Fully compatible with James extension mechanism.

âœ… Lightweight and integrates directly with its lifecycle.

âœ… Uses James mailbox/session APIs as intended.

